Step 1: Install Minikube (Windows)

Step 2: Verify Installation

	minikube version
	kubectl version --client
 
Step 3: Start Kubernetes Cluster

	minikube start

Step 4: Check Cluster Status

	minikube status
	kubectl cluster-info

Step 5: Check Nodes

	kubectl get nodes

Step 6: Create Your First Pod
🔹 Run an Nginx Pod
		kubectl run mypod --image=nginx
🔹 Check Pod Status
		kubectl get pods

Step 7: Describe Pod (Very Useful)
	kubectl describe pod mypod

Step 8: Delete Pod
	kubectl delete pod mypod 
    kubectl delete pods --all 	// to delete all Pods
// Here kubernetes self healing comes into action and action and heals it. 
So to permanently delete it you need to delete the deployment.
	kubectl delete deployment <deployment-name>

Step 9: Create Deployment (Real Way)
🧠 Deployment = Manages Pods automatically

	kubectl create deployment web --image=nginx
Check Deployment
	kubectl get deployments
	kubectl get pods

Step 10: Scale Application
🔹 Scale to 3 Pods
		kubectl scale deployment web --replicas=3
		kubectl get pods

Step 11: Scale Down
		kubectl scale deployment web --replicas=1

Step 12: Self Healing Demo
		kubectl delete pod <pod-name>

Step 13: Expose Application (Service)

🔹 Create Service
	kubectl expose deployment web --type=NodePort --port=80

Check Services
	kubectl get services

Step 14: Access Application in Browser
	minikube service web

Step 15: Delete Resources (Cleanup)
🔹 Delete Service
	kubectl delete service web
🔹 Delete Deployment
	kubectl delete deployment web

🛑 Step 16: Stop Cluster
	minikube stop

❌ Step 17: Delete Cluster Completely
	minikube delete

Execute command in Pod
	kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -- /bin/bash  // Access Pod's shell
	kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -- /bin/sh

View Pod logs
	kubectl logs <pod-name>

Create Pod from YAML
	kubectl apply -f <pod-name>.yaml